WEBVTT

00:17.225 --> 00:19.227
[classical music playing]

00:21.479 --> 00:23.106
[Marty] So where do we live?

00:24.107 --> 00:25.650
[Wendy] Look who's getting
ahead of himself.

00:25.734 --> 00:26.985
[Marty] How about Luxembourg?

00:28.111 --> 00:30.530
[Wendy] That's the best you've got?
Luxembourg?

00:32.657 --> 00:34.492
-[Marty] How about Santorini?
-[Wendy] No.

00:34.576 --> 00:37.579
-[Marty] No? Some white sand beaches?
-[Wendy] Mnh-mnh.

00:37.662 --> 00:42.375
Tourists. Steep inclines. Donkeys.

00:42.459 --> 00:45.378
[chattering]

00:45.462 --> 00:48.506
[Marty] There's Slugworth. Who's he with?

00:49.090 --> 00:51.384
[Wendy] Steve Simmons,
chief compliance officer.

00:51.468 --> 00:54.637
-[Marty] Hmm. Someone's been studying.
-[Wendy] You're surprised?

00:56.139 --> 00:57.348
[Marty] Who are the other two?

00:57.432 --> 01:00.310
[Wendy] State attorney general
and Leslie Ann Mackey.

01:00.852 --> 01:03.521
She's the founder
of Missourians for Morality.

01:05.231 --> 01:08.026
[Marty] Hanging out with the other
Missourians is probably more fun.

01:08.109 --> 01:10.737
[Wendy] Okay, be nice and play nice.

01:12.697 --> 01:14.324
Hyannis Port?

01:16.242 --> 01:19.245
-Are we the Kennedys now?
-Please.

01:19.329 --> 01:22.957
What do you think it was starting out as
a bootlegger in the real world, actually?

01:23.792 --> 01:24.834
The Gold Coast?

01:27.128 --> 01:30.090
Australia, Wendy? Come on.

01:30.173 --> 01:32.258
Nobody'd be looking for us in Australia.

01:32.342 --> 01:34.260
Yeah. No shit.

01:39.724 --> 01:41.142
-You got him?
-Mm-hmm.

01:45.230 --> 01:46.773
-Is he alone?
-Mm-hmm.

01:48.399 --> 01:49.567
[Marty] Are you ready?

01:50.485 --> 01:51.611
[Wendy] Mm-hmm.

01:53.947 --> 01:55.198
-Good luck.
-Mm-hmm.

02:24.519 --> 02:26.813
[Darlene] Jacob's angry with me.
I can tell.

02:27.981 --> 02:30.525
[sighs] Just feels different.

02:35.947 --> 02:39.492
I think maybe
I shouldn't have killed this Mexican.

02:41.286 --> 02:43.663
[Ash] The man disrespected you
in your own home.

02:46.416 --> 02:47.834
[grunts]

02:47.917 --> 02:50.461
Now, you know how much I admire Mr. Snell.

02:54.340 --> 02:55.967
[Darlene] Speak your mind, child.

02:57.051 --> 02:59.345
[Ash] Sometimes you have to agree
to disagree.

03:04.142 --> 03:05.393
That's part of the covenant.

03:07.812 --> 03:11.774
You're a sweet boy, Ash. You know that?

03:41.346 --> 03:42.513
[Jacob] Wendy.

03:43.264 --> 03:48.102
Jacob Snell. My wife, Darlene.
Our associate Ash.

03:48.186 --> 03:51.064
-[Darlene] Fresh from our hives.
-Thank you.

03:51.147 --> 03:51.981
Hi, there.

03:52.649 --> 03:54.984
-A moment?
-Yeah. Excuse me.

03:57.445 --> 04:00.573
-I take it she knows your business.
-Uh, yeah.

04:02.116 --> 04:06.704
Tricky thing, combining work and marriage,
but a blessing when it works.

04:06.788 --> 04:07.872
That's true.

04:08.748 --> 04:11.834
You have the keys
to our Mexican friend's vehicle?

04:11.918 --> 04:16.798
Yeah. Here you go. It's parked
around the bend, off the road a bit.

04:17.632 --> 04:19.759
Ash will drive it to Chicago.

04:19.842 --> 04:22.929
He's got the man's cell phone
and his credit cards.

04:23.012 --> 04:25.932
Okay. Just make sure you swipe one
of them when you get up there.

04:26.474 --> 04:28.142
As far the world will know,

04:28.226 --> 04:31.354
the man drove to Chicago
and fell off the face of God's Earth.

04:31.437 --> 04:35.024
Yeah, yeah. I left, like, three messages
on his cell phone.

04:35.108 --> 04:37.443
Call me back when you get there.
Make sure the cell towers--

04:37.527 --> 04:41.906
-This is a drill we're familiar with.
-Uh-huh. Okay. See you.

04:42.532 --> 04:45.994
[Darlene] You buckle up! Drive safe.

04:52.166 --> 04:55.753
Things happen.
You apologize and you move on.

04:57.547 --> 04:58.798
She blew a man's head off.

05:00.425 --> 05:02.093
For which she is contrite.

05:05.138 --> 05:06.639
Am I supposed to believe that?

05:07.598 --> 05:10.101
-The woman brought you fresh honey.
-Mm-hmm.

05:15.189 --> 05:16.566
[door opens]

05:24.073 --> 05:25.074
[exhales]

05:26.701 --> 05:28.119
Clean sheets again.

05:31.956 --> 05:33.666
I thought I'd feel different.

05:35.418 --> 05:38.338
Like we went around the world,
came back and everything had changed.

05:40.214 --> 05:41.674
I know that sounds stupid.

05:44.385 --> 05:49.515
I wouldn't have been as brave as you were
when that fucker was in the living room.

05:50.600 --> 05:52.185
I wouldn't have been able
to pull the trigger.

05:53.895 --> 05:55.313
Yes, you would have.

06:00.193 --> 06:01.903
I keep thinking about it.

06:04.489 --> 06:05.990
I would have just frozen.

06:11.496 --> 06:12.997
Mom told me to.

06:21.506 --> 06:23.257
Figured you should have half.

06:28.388 --> 06:30.598
Took it the night
we were putting it in the wall.

06:31.599 --> 06:33.059
I don't even know why I did it.

06:35.895 --> 06:38.606
-How much is it?
-Ten thousand.

06:41.901 --> 06:43.444
You think I should tell Mom and Dad?

06:44.028 --> 06:44.862
No.

06:48.658 --> 06:49.826
We might need it.

06:52.078 --> 06:53.538
[Charlotte sighs]

06:59.710 --> 07:01.963
[door opens and closes]

07:03.339 --> 07:05.842
[Ruth] I used to not even think
about the future.

07:07.051 --> 07:08.469
Because, you know...

07:09.720 --> 07:10.888
what was the point?

07:12.515 --> 07:17.645
So I'd get mad or get into trouble.

07:22.608 --> 07:24.986
But in the last few months, I've been...

07:26.654 --> 07:29.031
I've been tryin' to be a better person.

07:31.200 --> 07:35.746
Think about people besides just myself.

07:37.623 --> 07:40.334
You know, I got a real job,

07:41.461 --> 07:43.963
one with insurance and everything, and...

07:45.548 --> 07:50.386
I'm looking after two boys,
and I'm even thinking about their futures.

07:53.055 --> 07:53.890
[inhales]

07:55.141 --> 07:58.227
But I know I gotta keep myself right.

07:59.645 --> 08:02.148
Because if I don't, I'll lose everything.

08:06.486 --> 08:10.156
And I don't think any
of that would be possible

08:11.491 --> 08:13.576
if it wasn't for my dad.

08:13.659 --> 08:14.994
[breathes deeply]

08:20.249 --> 08:23.002
I've been coming
to visit him regular and...

08:25.254 --> 08:27.882
And I know how bad he wants to do good.

08:29.258 --> 08:31.302
Thank you, Miss Langmore.

08:32.470 --> 08:35.097
Though it's important
for this parole board

08:35.181 --> 08:37.183
to consider the inmate's character,

08:37.266 --> 08:41.270
it's also important to consider
the question, "Why now?"

08:45.191 --> 08:46.192
Yes, ma'am.

08:49.445 --> 08:50.696
[Ruth] <i>Like I said,</i>

08:51.697 --> 08:56.744
<i>I'm becoming the guardian of two boys,</i>
<i>my cousins,</i>

08:56.827 --> 08:59.705
<i>who recently lost their dad.</i>

09:02.250 --> 09:04.460
<i>And I'm tryin' my best every day.</i>

09:06.295 --> 09:08.214
<i>But I'm just a young girl.</i>

09:11.342 --> 09:13.803
<i>I know what it means to need a daddy.</i>

09:32.697 --> 09:33.614
[Tuck] Hey, Marty!

09:34.991 --> 09:36.701
Hey, Tuck. What's going on?

09:37.451 --> 09:42.415
Everything's locked.
Down here and by the front door, too.

09:42.498 --> 09:44.208
Yeah? Did you try Rachel?

09:44.292 --> 09:47.837
It goes straight to her voicemail.
Just like yesterday.

09:48.921 --> 09:51.591
-Yesterday, too, huh?
-Yes.

09:57.221 --> 10:00.558
-Um, is your mom and sister home?
-Yes.

10:00.641 --> 10:03.644
Why don't you head home? I'll call you
when I need you for work, okay?

10:03.728 --> 10:04.770
Okay.

10:14.655 --> 10:15.990
[breathes deeply]

10:17.199 --> 10:18.159
Fuck!

10:55.946 --> 10:57.281
-[Harry] Mrs. Byrde?
-Oh.

10:58.157 --> 11:00.618
[chuckles] Harry, you scared me.

11:00.701 --> 11:03.954
-Can I help you with something?
-Yes.

11:04.038 --> 11:07.750
I was wondering. Why do we use the freezer

11:07.833 --> 11:10.294
when embalmed bodies don't need
to be refrigerated?

11:12.046 --> 11:13.047
Coolers.

11:14.382 --> 11:15.758
[Wendy] I'm sorry.

11:15.841 --> 11:19.637
They're called coolers, not freezers.
In the funeral game.

11:19.720 --> 11:21.013
That notwithstanding,

11:21.097 --> 11:24.600
I think we could save an enormous amount
of moneyÂ on refrigeration costs

11:24.684 --> 11:27.311
if we turned the coolers
into storage units.

11:30.147 --> 11:31.148
I'll buy the locks myself.

11:32.066 --> 11:33.067
[Harry] Of course.

11:34.652 --> 11:36.028
Also, I was thinking...

11:36.112 --> 11:38.906
We should probably buy some more caskets.

11:38.989 --> 11:41.534
In bulk. To save money. Say 25?

11:46.664 --> 11:49.041
-I need to borrow the hearse.
-I'm sorry.

11:50.543 --> 11:55.464
We have a terminally ill tenant.
He wants to test drive his final ride.

11:58.008 --> 11:59.468
That's okay, isn't it?

12:00.469 --> 12:01.470
Well...

12:02.096 --> 12:05.891
[stammering] it's all highly unusual.

12:09.145 --> 12:09.979
Hmm.

12:21.073 --> 12:23.242
Don't seem so fucking glad to see me.

12:24.201 --> 12:25.661
I'm expecting somebody else.

12:26.912 --> 12:28.456
I've been callin'.

12:28.539 --> 12:29.749
And I've been busy.

12:31.917 --> 12:33.669
We need to talk about my future.

12:35.671 --> 12:37.840
I can't talk right now, okay?

12:37.923 --> 12:40.634
Wyatt's got to go to college.
You have any idea what college costs?

12:40.718 --> 12:42.386
-Yeah, I got a pretty good idea.
-A shit ton.

12:42.470 --> 12:44.972
-I'm serious. This is not a good time
-A shit ton.

12:45.055 --> 12:46.807
for us to talk, okay?

12:50.436 --> 12:55.274
I was thinkin', you and me,
we could be partners.

12:56.692 --> 12:58.527
What I meant was, not now.

12:59.487 --> 13:00.446
No, stay in the car.

13:00.529 --> 13:03.991
At least I can get a percentage!
I think I fucking earned it, Marty!

13:04.074 --> 13:07.119
-You gotta pump the brakes a bit--
-I'm not fucking stupid!

13:07.203 --> 13:12.124
I know that the cartels are gonna
eventually dump another pile

13:12.208 --> 13:13.876
of shit money on you!

13:16.378 --> 13:17.296
We'll see.

13:19.215 --> 13:23.844
We'll see. I promise we'll talk, okay?
I promise.

13:27.848 --> 13:29.141
Nice whip.

13:33.354 --> 13:36.440
-What was that about?
-Her uncles.

13:40.736 --> 13:42.363
Any idea how much she took?

13:42.822 --> 13:44.865
No. We're just gonna have to
count it all

13:44.949 --> 13:48.118
and pray to God we can absorb the loss
without the cartel finding out.

13:48.202 --> 13:49.912
It's gonna take half the night
to move all this.

13:49.995 --> 13:53.332
Yeah, well, she fucked us.
She fucked us and now she's...

13:55.125 --> 13:56.585
She fucked us.

13:56.669 --> 13:58.295
What did you tell the kids?

13:59.213 --> 14:02.383
Just that we had to work late,
not to stay up. Buddy's with them.

14:05.469 --> 14:09.139
Wendy, I know.
I know. Let's just get started.

14:38.669 --> 14:39.503
Hey.

14:40.796 --> 14:41.755
Hey.

14:44.091 --> 14:46.343
-I'm just gonna be in here, all right?
-Yeah, I'll be right over.

14:47.803 --> 14:48.721
Hey.

14:49.305 --> 14:50.139
What?

14:52.933 --> 14:54.143
I hope you're using a rubber.

14:55.311 --> 14:57.605
Come on, it's not like that.
We just hang out.

14:58.981 --> 15:00.357
Fixing it up for your dad?

15:01.317 --> 15:02.318
Yeah.

15:04.194 --> 15:05.446
It's gonna be okay.

15:06.363 --> 15:10.492
I know. I just want him to have
a nice place. [chuckles]

15:11.327 --> 15:12.286
Start straight.

15:12.369 --> 15:14.455
Well, just saying you're not alone.

15:23.547 --> 15:26.425
[growling]

15:30.679 --> 15:32.139
You dicks go to bed.

15:38.896 --> 15:40.773
[Jonah] Have you seen
my humanities folder?

15:40.856 --> 15:42.942
[Wendy] It's next to the TV.

15:43.025 --> 15:45.277
[Marty] Guys, tell me one more time
where you were last week

15:45.361 --> 15:46.445
when you were out of school.

15:46.528 --> 15:48.364
[Charlotte] At a funeral
in North Carolina.

15:48.447 --> 15:49.531
[Marty] Yep. For who?

15:51.575 --> 15:53.911
-Great-Aunt Tyra.
-[Marty] Yep.

15:54.662 --> 15:57.414
[Charlotte] Think we could start making
chai instead of coffee?

15:57.498 --> 16:00.376
Maybe matcha?
You know, something macrobiotic.

16:00.960 --> 16:03.462
-Do we even have a Great-Aunt Tyra?
-Yeah, unfortunately.

16:03.545 --> 16:07.591
Before you ask, don't worry.
I'll replace your phone this afternoon.

16:07.675 --> 16:11.470
Guys, this is a new baseline, okay?
We're gonna build normal from here.

16:12.054 --> 16:13.055
We're out of danger?

16:13.389 --> 16:17.935
Uh, yes. But everything from now on
needs to be about keeping it that way.

16:18.018 --> 16:20.479
Which means we need 100% honesty.

16:20.562 --> 16:23.107
Like our lives depend on it.
You understand that?

16:26.068 --> 16:27.069
Yeah.

16:28.904 --> 16:31.448
-Why is Buddy here?
-Buddy's not deaf.

16:31.532 --> 16:34.493
Buddy's gonna oversee the installation
of a security system this morning.

16:34.576 --> 16:36.328
Plus, we need to get that window replaced.

16:36.412 --> 16:40.165
Yeah, next time I'll aim lower,
shoot 'em in the ball sack,

16:40.249 --> 16:42.001
avoid the shattered glass.

16:42.543 --> 16:43.836
What happened to the body?

16:44.503 --> 16:47.089
We took it to the funeral parlor.
We cremated it.

16:47.172 --> 16:48.465
[Charlotte] What funeral parlor?

16:49.133 --> 16:50.884
I bought one before we left town.

16:51.677 --> 16:52.845
You bought a funeral parlor?

16:52.928 --> 16:54.138
-[Wendy] Uh-huh.
-[cellphone chiming]

16:54.221 --> 16:55.556
Have you killed other people?

16:55.639 --> 16:57.391
-Of course not.
-We do not kill people.

16:57.474 --> 16:59.977
Guys, that's it. Please, to school.
Learning. Hello.

17:01.854 --> 17:02.688
Yeah.

17:04.148 --> 17:04.982
Okay.

17:08.110 --> 17:09.361
I understand.

17:10.446 --> 17:11.572
Yeah, bye.

17:13.949 --> 17:15.200
[Charlotte] Is everything okay?

17:16.660 --> 17:17.953
Total honesty.

17:18.996 --> 17:24.376
Yeah, everything's great. In fact,
our casino project has its first meeting.

17:26.378 --> 17:28.505
Oh. They're here.

17:30.299 --> 17:31.842
All right. Everyone in the car.

17:37.014 --> 17:38.724
They should have come to us.

17:40.517 --> 17:42.144
This is neutral territory.

17:43.312 --> 17:46.148
It's a lack of respect and trust,
is what it is.

17:47.441 --> 17:53.280
Well, just... Everybody stay calm, okay?
This is a simple business arrangement.

17:54.364 --> 17:56.909
All of life's
a simple business arrangement.

17:57.367 --> 17:59.620
That's why you prepare for anything.

18:22.976 --> 18:24.895
-You must be Marty Byrde.
-Yeah.

18:24.978 --> 18:26.855
Helen Pierce.
I'm the attorney for your employer.

18:29.566 --> 18:32.027
Jacob Snell. My wife Darlene.

18:37.407 --> 18:38.700
Where's Del?

18:40.744 --> 18:42.287
I was hoping you could tell me.

18:44.123 --> 18:45.624
Oh. Uh...

18:46.542 --> 18:47.835
I assumed he'd be here.

18:51.505 --> 18:55.134
We can't seem to locate him.
Last we heard, he was in Chicago.

18:55.968 --> 18:59.221
Okay. Well, what does that mean?

19:00.264 --> 19:01.765
[Helen] It means we endeavor without him.

19:03.142 --> 19:06.353
Trust me when I tell you that
my client has a very deep bench.

19:08.355 --> 19:09.189
Yeah.

19:09.565 --> 19:11.859
Should we go inside?
Discuss things more casually?

19:13.485 --> 19:14.486
Good.

19:17.197 --> 19:19.950
<i>My client is prepared to offer</i>
<i>an 80-20 split.</i>

19:20.909 --> 19:22.119
[Darlene] <i>In whose favor?</i>

19:24.079 --> 19:30.419
Seems to me that 80-20 in either direction
doesn't exactly speak to a partnership.

19:31.420 --> 19:34.798
My client appreciates what a project
this size must mean for you.

19:35.215 --> 19:38.719
You're donating your land,
but he's the one incurring all the risk.

19:38.802 --> 19:40.554
-[Darlene] His risk?
-That's right.

19:41.138 --> 19:42.723
From a pueblo in Mexico.

19:43.307 --> 19:44.766
Financial risk.

19:44.850 --> 19:48.312
Well, there's certainly plenty of risk
to go around.

19:48.896 --> 19:52.024
Not to mention the potential loss
of reputation to my client

19:52.107 --> 19:54.735
if he distributes
a product that's inferior.

19:57.029 --> 19:58.030
In...

20:00.115 --> 20:04.578
[chuckles] I've been patient,
and I have been respectful.

20:08.373 --> 20:11.627
I suggest you do the same
when you're talkin' about my business.

20:13.378 --> 20:17.007
I am simply suggesting
that all farms are unique.

20:17.424 --> 20:18.675
Quality can vary.

20:20.469 --> 20:21.386
Uh-huh.

20:26.892 --> 20:29.645
That can be tested, right? The quality?

20:30.395 --> 20:33.190
Quite frankly,
my client and I both have doubts

20:33.273 --> 20:35.442
you can even deliver this casino.

20:36.360 --> 20:37.778
Okay. Why is that?

20:37.861 --> 20:40.614
'Cause Missouri has a cap on the number
of casinos allowed to open?

20:41.406 --> 20:45.035
[Helen] Or the fact that the casino has
to be actually physically completed

20:45.118 --> 20:46.912
before a bid can be approved?

20:46.995 --> 20:49.581
Which creates a huge financial risk
for most people,

20:49.665 --> 20:54.670
but provides an opportunity
to move cash for us.

20:54.753 --> 20:58.674
Don't forget about the political campaign
needed to overturn that cap.

20:59.341 --> 21:01.843
It would take a seasoned pro, right?

21:02.261 --> 21:05.055
Someone like, say, my wife.

21:06.556 --> 21:11.186
So, my job is to deliver a casino.
I can do that.

21:11.270 --> 21:12.771
You just need to make a fair deal.

21:17.359 --> 21:20.237
And to be clear,
I'm gonna be taking 3% of the profits.

21:20.570 --> 21:22.781
Okay? That's my customary fee.

21:22.864 --> 21:25.284
I don't want anyone to think I'm being
anything less than transparent.

21:26.827 --> 21:30.038
You do realize you're betting everything
on being able to pull this off.

21:30.664 --> 21:33.166
Yeah.
Six months you're gonna have a casino.

21:37.212 --> 21:39.214
Let me ask you, for the record,

21:39.298 --> 21:42.092
did Del say anything to you
about going to Chicago?

21:43.010 --> 21:43.844
No.

21:43.927 --> 21:46.888
Because he was scheduled
on a private jet to Mexico City.

21:46.972 --> 21:49.266
Changing plans would have been
a breach of trust.

21:50.100 --> 21:52.769
My client is a man
who demands absolute trust,

21:52.853 --> 21:54.604
as I'm sure you can appreciate.

21:55.605 --> 21:56.940
Of course.

21:57.024 --> 22:01.278
Don't fuck with me.
And don't fuck with my client. Understand?

22:03.780 --> 22:05.407
They'll kill your children.

22:05.490 --> 22:07.451
They'll gut your fucking wife.

22:09.870 --> 22:12.122
Do you want me to tell you
what they'll do to you?

22:16.335 --> 22:17.502
Okay.

22:20.130 --> 22:21.340
This was productive.

22:26.762 --> 22:27.763
[Wendy] Well?

22:29.806 --> 22:32.351
The last they heard, Del was in Chicago.

22:32.893 --> 22:34.770
[Wendy exhales]

22:38.607 --> 22:40.400
11:30 in the morning.

22:42.611 --> 22:45.489
Now we just have to pull off
opening a fucking casino.

22:54.247 --> 22:56.249
[upbeat music playing]

23:04.132 --> 23:06.635
[Rose] I don't wanna get
a bitch in trouble,

23:06.718 --> 23:10.055
but Cheyenne, she's turning tricks
in the VIP room again.

23:18.688 --> 23:19.815
[Cheyenne moaning]

23:19.898 --> 23:21.983
-What the fuck? Get off!
-[Cheyenne screams]

