41:26.650 --> 41:29.028
and I'd love to take a look
at your security footage.

41:29.111 --> 41:31.071
I can give you precise date and time.

41:31.697 --> 41:32.781
I can't do that.

41:32.865 --> 41:35.451
His card was actually used
without his knowledge.

41:35.910 --> 41:37.036
Like I said...

41:37.912 --> 41:39.455
I'm his attorney.

41:40.456 --> 41:44.043
We're trying to conduct this investigation
as discreetly as possible.

41:44.126 --> 41:45.878
I'm sure you understand.

41:47.046 --> 41:50.174
What part of "I can't do that"
is so fucking confusing?

41:56.055 --> 41:58.098
Are all the files kept in that recorder?

41:59.016 --> 41:59.850
Why?

42:00.184 --> 42:03.187
I'm just curious
if they're sent to another server

42:03.270 --> 42:04.855
or if you're my only recourse.

42:04.939 --> 42:06.023
[clears throat]

42:06.106 --> 42:08.234
No. You are stuck with me.

42:10.361 --> 42:13.280
I would be more than happy
to pay for any inconvenience.

42:16.575 --> 42:19.161
How's 500 grand?

42:20.162 --> 42:22.540
I'm sorry we couldn't come
to an agreement.

42:43.727 --> 42:47.147
Dude, if you're with that bitch,
I already said everything I had to say.

42:49.441 --> 42:50.317
Hey.

42:52.653 --> 42:55.447
No, no, no, no, no. No, no.

42:59.285 --> 43:00.578
Don't kill me.

43:08.210 --> 43:09.587
[man groaning]

43:09.670 --> 43:11.005
[door closes]

43:13.132 --> 43:14.717
[door opens]

43:28.230 --> 43:29.648
[man gags]

43:31.066 --> 43:32.318
How about now?

43:44.246 --> 43:48.000
Tell me. How does a casino equate
to a more simple family life?

43:49.918 --> 43:55.257
What we do for a living has
absolutely no bearing on how we parent.

43:55.341 --> 43:56.717
And I refute anybody

43:56.800 --> 43:59.762
who says Christian values
and capitalism can't coexist.

44:02.306 --> 44:03.140
[Marty] Hmm.

44:03.974 --> 44:04.808
[Wendy] Hmm?

44:05.434 --> 44:06.852
We are new to Missouri,

44:06.935 --> 44:10.898
but we understand business,
and we understand the power of community.

44:13.233 --> 44:15.444
You said you worked in politics
in Chicago?

44:16.153 --> 44:16.987
I did.

44:17.613 --> 44:19.490
[Wilkes] And you think
you can sell me on this idea.

44:19.573 --> 44:21.450
-I do.
-[Wilkes] Yeah?

44:24.078 --> 44:25.329
Enlighten me.

44:28.415 --> 44:33.796
Well, as Marty sort of
skimmed the surface...

44:33.879 --> 44:37.007
[panting]

44:42.513 --> 44:44.056
-Ow.
-[both chuckle]

44:44.139 --> 44:45.474
-Careful.
-[laughs]

44:45.557 --> 44:49.853
Don't you dent my top-ranked minivan
in the US, okay?

45:07.621 --> 45:09.206
Let's go. Out of the car.

45:09.289 --> 45:10.541
Out of the car.

45:12.876 --> 45:13.877
In the back seat.

45:29.143 --> 45:29.977
You lied.

45:33.522 --> 45:36.608
This is Del's credit card being used
in Chicago.

45:37.818 --> 45:41.488
I'm sure you can recognize that gentleman.
He's rather distinctive.

45:46.785 --> 45:48.454
Distinctively not Del.

45:52.124 --> 45:54.877
-I had no idea--
-[Helen] Oh, please.

45:54.960 --> 45:56.295
For both our sakes.

45:57.129 --> 45:59.006
We know you are not a killer.

46:00.340 --> 46:01.800
You're a businessman,

46:02.801 --> 46:07.639
which is why we are giving you an hour
to negotiate reparations for Del's death.

46:09.099 --> 46:11.018
-One hour?
-Mm-hmm.

46:12.019 --> 46:14.813
After that, I have to leave it
to my associates outside.

46:17.566 --> 46:19.234
[Marty] Uh, well...

46:23.197 --> 46:25.282
Del was completely out of line.

46:25.365 --> 46:29.453
We had a deal made
and then he started insulting the Snells.

46:29.536 --> 46:32.247
I don't doubt it. I knew Del.

46:33.373 --> 46:34.625
Nevertheless.

46:39.171 --> 46:40.964
What kind of deal
are you willing to accept?

46:42.424 --> 46:44.343
I'll know it when I hear it.

46:46.762 --> 46:47.763
Okay.

46:49.890 --> 46:50.849
Okay.

46:51.809 --> 46:53.227
Let's go see the Snells.

46:54.895 --> 46:55.729
Good.

46:56.313 --> 46:57.606
[all laughing]

46:58.857 --> 47:00.359
[Wyatt] So were you ever scared in there?

47:01.485 --> 47:04.988
[Cade] Most of those boys don't really
fight, they just push and shove.

47:07.783 --> 47:08.992
But forget about me.

47:09.993 --> 47:12.913
Tell me about you, boy.
How's that local talent?

47:13.997 --> 47:17.125
-What are you talking about?
-Girls. Lakeside.

47:18.585 --> 47:20.212
You managing to get your share?

47:20.295 --> 47:22.548
[Wyatt] They don't pay
much attention to me.

47:22.631 --> 47:26.176
None of 'em? There must be at least one
with some sense.

47:26.635 --> 47:29.054
I don't know. Maybe one.

47:30.097 --> 47:31.431
[laughing]

47:32.891 --> 47:34.226
[Cade] Do tell.

47:34.643 --> 47:36.186
[Ruth] You need to go to sleep.

47:36.812 --> 47:38.230
It's a fucking school night.

47:38.814 --> 47:39.773
[Cade] Tell you what.

47:40.607 --> 47:44.069
We'll do a little business together,
put some money in your pocket,

47:44.611 --> 47:46.113
let the girls notice...

47:46.780 --> 47:48.073
that bulge.

47:48.156 --> 47:50.742
[both laughing]

47:51.827 --> 47:53.704
-[Ruth] Classy.
-[chuckling] Oh! Whoa!

47:54.997 --> 47:56.832
[Ruth] You're not supposed
to drink on parole.

47:56.915 --> 47:59.585
Hmm. Girl thinks
she's both our mamas.

48:04.882 --> 48:05.716
So...

48:06.925 --> 48:09.303
what do you think happened
to your daddy, anyway?

48:09.386 --> 48:13.015
How's he careless enough to go
and get himself electrocuted?

48:13.098 --> 48:14.641
That's not like him.

48:17.060 --> 48:19.104
Yeah. I don't know.

48:19.897 --> 48:21.773
Probably Boyd did something stupid.

48:21.857 --> 48:22.983
[Cade] Yeah.

48:23.650 --> 48:24.568
Mm-hmm.

48:25.110 --> 48:26.653
Maybe it was Boyd.

48:30.407 --> 48:34.870
Fuck it. I'm going to bed.
Don't blame me if your mornings are shit.

48:38.123 --> 48:40.000
-[Wyatt] Night!
-Night.

48:41.335 --> 48:42.961
[Jacob] <i>What are they asking for?</i>

48:44.046 --> 48:45.339
Fair reparations.

48:46.048 --> 48:47.966
The man violated a code.

48:49.384 --> 48:52.012
The man was a top lieutenant
in a billion dollar business.

48:54.306 --> 48:55.474
Thank you, Ash.

49:00.896 --> 49:02.439
What are you suggesting?

49:03.607 --> 49:05.567
You should offer them $5 million.

49:06.985 --> 49:10.280
-For that Mexican man?
-[Wendy] Del had a wife and two children.

49:10.364 --> 49:11.406
They're better off without him.

49:12.741 --> 49:14.451
[Marty] We can't leave here
without a solution.

49:15.035 --> 49:17.496
[Darlene] There's nothing needs solving.

49:17.579 --> 49:20.832
I take it they didn't give you
clear guidelines.

49:23.919 --> 49:24.920
What about $4 million?

49:30.175 --> 49:33.303
[Wendy] What if you adjusted
your percentage in the casino?

49:33.971 --> 49:36.598
Nothing comes out of your pocket
until it makes money.

49:41.019 --> 49:45.899
5%? 3%. That'd pay for
any misunderstanding in perpetuity.

49:45.983 --> 49:47.150
[Darlene] It's weakness.

49:47.234 --> 49:48.068
[Wendy] Your heroin.

49:49.152 --> 49:52.114
Maybe you surrender profits
on a certain number of shipments.

49:52.197 --> 49:55.033
They'd still need to provide distribution.

49:55.117 --> 49:56.535
[Marty] We could negotiate that.

49:56.618 --> 50:00.580
[Darlene] Giving away our crop for free
goes against the backbone of this deal.

50:00.664 --> 50:02.332
You shot their man's fucking head off.

50:03.041 --> 50:06.336
[Jacob] The man violated a code.
That has a price...

50:07.713 --> 50:09.464
but it's not ours to pay.

50:17.472 --> 50:19.141
Jacob, there are Mexicans at your gate

50:19.224 --> 50:22.227
that are ready to come up here
and wipe us all out.

50:22.310 --> 50:23.854
[Darlene] Let 'em come.

50:25.814 --> 50:27.774
[Wendy] You have got
to think this through.

50:29.609 --> 50:33.405
The cartel has more men and more guns
than you could ever have,

50:33.488 --> 50:37.117
and if it doesn't happen tonight,
they'll just send more men.

50:37.200 --> 50:40.620
More and more and more.
So, I'm begging you.

50:42.831 --> 50:44.583
We are begging you. We have two children.

50:44.666 --> 50:49.296
So, I ask you, just see this through.
Just think it through.

50:50.839 --> 50:52.049
You need to go.

50:53.842 --> 50:54.718
Go.

51:00.348 --> 51:01.683
Don't do this.

51:01.767 --> 51:04.770
[Jacob] No more compromises,
no more deals.

51:05.645 --> 51:09.191
Ash, escort them out. Get the men.

51:12.903 --> 51:15.030
-[grunts]
-[Wendy yells] Oh!

51:22.079 --> 51:24.122
-[Wendy gasping] Oh, God.
-[Marty] Jesus Christ.

51:24.206 --> 51:25.207
[Darlene] No!

51:26.208 --> 51:28.919
Jacob! No! No!

51:29.002 --> 51:31.046
[gasps] Ash! Ash!

51:31.129 --> 51:33.715
[breathing heavily]

51:33.799 --> 51:35.425
[Marty] Jesus Christ, Jacob.

51:36.635 --> 51:37.636
What the fuck?

51:38.220 --> 51:39.304
Why, Jacob?

51:40.055 --> 51:41.098
No. Ash.

51:41.181 --> 51:43.058
You killed their man, Darlene.

51:43.141 --> 51:46.144
-[Darlene whimpering] Shit.
-Go on.

51:46.269 --> 51:48.688
This was the only thing
that was gonna make it right.

51:48.772 --> 51:49.981
And you know it.

51:52.776 --> 51:54.486
Now, go get your Mexican.

51:55.278 --> 51:56.363
[Darlene sighs]

51:57.989 --> 52:00.075
[Marty] Come on. Yeah.

52:05.122 --> 52:06.748
[Wendy] Excuse me. I'm sorry.

52:48.665 --> 52:50.083
Is that what we wanted?

52:55.505 --> 52:57.299
We didn't want anything.

53:02.345 --> 53:03.430
[Wendy] So, that's it?

53:05.182 --> 53:08.268
We go back in that house, go to bed,
wake up in the morning, kiss the kids?

53:11.855 --> 53:13.773
That's exactly what we do.

53:14.608 --> 53:18.236
We make the pancakes, and ask the kids
what's going on with school

53:18.320 --> 53:21.698
and we just keep trying to figure out
a way out of this, Wendy.

53:21.781 --> 53:23.033
We're responsible.

53:24.284 --> 53:25.785
-What for?
-All of it.

53:25.869 --> 53:26.703
No, we're not.

53:26.786 --> 53:29.539
-Another man is dead.
-Because of his choices.

53:29.623 --> 53:32.751
He didn't have to try
to cover up a murder, okay?

53:32.834 --> 53:35.837
Just like Darlene didn't have to
kill Del in the first place,

53:35.921 --> 53:39.674
or Russ and Boyd didn't have to decide
to try to kill me,

53:39.758 --> 53:42.886
or Mason should have stayed out
on the water.

53:42.969 --> 53:45.180
Should've stayed on the fucking water.

53:45.722 --> 53:47.432
And, you know...

53:48.683 --> 53:51.519
People make choices, Wendy.
Choices have consequences.

53:51.603 --> 53:54.064
We don't have to live
under the weight of those decisions.

53:55.690 --> 53:57.734
At least admit it was good for us.

54:01.071 --> 54:03.740
If that man hadn't died,
the casino would be dead.

54:04.908 --> 54:06.076
So would we.

54:10.247 --> 54:11.373
We got lucky.

54:56.251 --> 54:57.460
What'd he want?

55:01.756 --> 55:04.509
-Who?
-Byrde.

55:05.593 --> 55:07.470
Why'd he show up here like that?

55:10.265 --> 55:12.142
I asked him for a raise.

55:19.774 --> 55:21.776
[Cade sighs]

55:29.659 --> 55:30.952
[grunts]

55:32.579 --> 55:35.123
[breathing heavily]

55:36.374 --> 55:37.625
